[0.000, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[1d; only output the code'\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[1m\u001b[2;161HThinking...\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[3;161HThinking Process:\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[4;161H\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\n1.  **Goal:** Implement Depth-First Search (DFS) in Python.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[6;161H2.  **Constraint:** Style must be compact.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[7;161H3.  **Constraint:** Output must *only* be the code.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[8;161H4.  **DFS Implementation:** DFS typically uses a stack (or recursion, \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[9;161Hwhich uses the call stack). Using recursion is generally the most compact \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[10;161Hand \"Pythonic\" way to write DFS unless memory constraints are severe or \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[11;161Hthe graph is extremely deep.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[12;161H5.  **Structure (Graph Representation):** I'll assume the graph is \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[13;161Hrepresented using an adjacency list (dictionary mapping nodes to lists of \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[14;161Hneighbors).\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[15;161H6.  **Core Logic (Recursive DFS):**\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[16;161H    *   Need a function `dfs(graph, start_node, visited)`.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[17;161H    *   Mark `start_node` as visited.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[18;161H    *   Process `start_node` (e.g., print it).\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[19;161H    *   For each neighbor `v` of `start_node`:\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[20;161H        *   If `v` is not visited:\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[21;161H            *   Recursively call `dfs(graph, v, visited)`.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[22;161H\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\n7.  **Refining for Compactness (Python):**\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[24;161H    *   I'll wrap it in a class or a self-contained function, but a \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[25;161Hfunction is simpler for a compact example.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[26;161H    *   I need to handle the graph setup and calling mechanism cleanly.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[27;161H\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\n*(Self-Correction/Refinement: To make it compact, I will use a function \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[29;161Hthat takes the graph and the starting node, and I will use a set for \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[30;161H`visited` checks.)*\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[31;161H\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\n8.  **Final Code Structure (Using recursion for maximum compactness):**\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[33;161H\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\n```python\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[35;161Hdef dfs(graph, start):\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[36;161H    visited = set()\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[37;161H    # Use a stack/list for explicit traversal if avoiding recursion depth \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[38;161Hlimit,\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[39;161H    # but recursion is more compact conceptually. Let's stick to \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[40;161Hrecursion.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[41;161H\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\n    def explore(node):\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[43;161H        if node not in visited:\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[44;161H            print(node) # Action to perform on visiting\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[45;161H            visited.add(node)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[46;161H            for neighbor in graph.get(node, []):\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[47;161H                explore(neighbor)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[48;161H\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\n    explore(start)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[50;161H\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\n# Example usage setup\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[52;161H# graph = { ... }\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[53;161H# dfs(graph, 'A')\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[54;161H```\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[55;161H\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\n(I will simplify the final output by making it a single self-contained \u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[57;161Hset of functions/logic, demonstrating the core recursive pattern.)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[1m\u001b[58;161H...done thinking.\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\u001b[59;161H\u001b[K\n```python\u001b[K\u001b[61;161Hdef dfs(graph, start_node):\u001b[K\u001b[62;161H    \"\"\"Performs Depth-First Search on a graph represented by an adjacency \u001b[K\u001b[63;161Hdictionary.\"\"\"\u001b[K\u001b[64;161H\u001b[K\u001b[34h\u001b[?25h"]
